article.headline: Bryant 103, Quinnipiac 95
article.story: SMITHFIELD, R.I. -- Frankie Dobbs scored 24 points and surpassed 1,000 in his career, and Bryant pulled away in the second half to beat Quinnipiac 103-95 on Thursday night in Northeast Conference play. Dyami Starks had 20 points, Alex Francis 16, Corey Maynard 14 and Vlad Kondratyev 13 for the Bulldogs (10-4, 3-0), who guaranteed their first 10-win season since joining Division I in 2008. Ike Azotam scored 21 points for the Bobcats (5-9, 1-2), while Jamee Jackson had 15, Kendrick Ray 12 and Ousmane Drame 10. Bryant shot 63.2 percent from beyond the arc (12 of 19) to Quinnipiac's 25 percent (3 of 12) and outscored the Bobcats 23-10 from the foul line. Quinnipiac closed to 64-68 on Drame's jumper with 10:52 to go, but the Bulldogs ran off 10 consecutive points for a 78-64 lead at 8:34 on the strength of three layups from Kondratyev and were never threatened.
